---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is AH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points"
  description="AH is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (A=1, H=4). An exclamation of realization or surprise. Extension: AHS. Free word checker."
  keywords="is ah a scrabble word, ah scrabble, ah valid word, ah points scrabble, two letter words with h, ahs scrabble, ah definition"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is AH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points",
    "description": "AH is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (A=1, H=4). An exclamation of realization.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ah-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is AH a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! AH is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (international) dictionaries. It scores 5 points (A=1, H=4) and is an exclamation expressing realization, satisfaction, or surprise. It's one of the key 2-letter words for placing the H tile." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can AH be pluralized in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — AHS is valid and scores 6 points. This is useful because it means AH can be extended by adding S at the end, making it hookable. You can play AH first, then hook an S on a later turn for additional scoring." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What other 2-letter H words exist in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are several 2-letter words with H: AH (5pts), EH (5pts), OH (5pts), UH (5pts), HA (5pts), HE (5pts), HI (5pts), HO (5pts), HM (7pts), and SH (5pts). HM scores highest at 7 points. Knowing all H two-letter words gives you flexibility for parallel plays." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Checker</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Green Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AH — 5 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">A=1, H=4 · Valid in TWL ✓ · Valid in SOWPODS ✓</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An exclamation of realization, relief, or satisfaction. One of the essential 2-letter H words that opens up parallel plays and helps place the 4-point H tile efficiently.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">H=4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Key Tile</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">AHS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Plural Form</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dictionaries</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Definition & Usage</h2>
      <p>AH is an interjection expressing realization ("ah, I see!"), relief ("ah, that's better"), or satisfaction. It can also express wonder or surprise. As a noun, it refers to the exclamation itself — hence the plural AHS ("there were many ahs from the audience").</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Dictionary Entry</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-medium">AH</span> (interjection/noun) — used to express surprise, joy, pity, realization, or pain. Plural: <span class="text-white font-medium">AHS</span>. Sometimes spelled "aah" for a drawn-out version (also valid as AAH in Scrabble).</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Extensions & Hooks</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AHS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YAH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">H on premium squares:</span> Place H on a DLS for 9 points from just AH (H×2=8, A=1). On a TLS, H alone contributes 12 points to the word. AH is your shortest path to H premium square bonuses.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play power:</span> AH played alongside an existing word creates crossword scores on both letters. If A touches a high-value letter above, you score both words in one play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front hook variety:</span> BAH, DAH, PAH, RAH, YAH — AH accepts many front hooks. Play AH first, then extend with a consonant on your next turn for double scoring opportunities.</p></div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ha-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is HA a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-uh-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is UH a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble word checker, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
